178
00:12:31,346 --> 00:12:34,346
Pops, can you try moving this statue?

179
00:12:34,346 --> 00:12:36,246
What? It's a statue.

180
00:12:36,246 --> 00:12:37,746
What makes you think I can move it?

181
00:12:37,746 --> 00:12:41,146
Don't you think there's something strange about this statue?

182
00:12:41,146 --> 00:12:42,446
What?

183
00:12:42,446 --> 00:12:45,346
Your mustache that's not supposed to be connected

184
00:12:45,346 --> 00:12:46,746
is actually connected.

185
00:12:46,746 --> 00:12:48,946
It looks like it's a fake.

186
00:12:51,646 --> 00:12:52,646
What?

187
00:12:52,646 --> 00:12:54,246
Is this it?

188
00:12:56,046 --> 00:12:58,746
What? There's nothing here.

189
00:13:03,946 --> 00:13:06,046
That sound...

190
00:13:06,046 --> 00:13:07,046
I get it!

191
00:13:07,046 --> 00:13:08,246
What?

192
00:13:10,546 --> 00:13:12,246
Lend this to me for a while, okay?

193
00:13:14,446 --> 00:13:18,046
I see, so that's what happened.

194
00:13:18,046 --> 00:13:19,446
What?

195
00:13:19,446 --> 00:13:22,446
What're you doing here, Conan?

196
00:13:22,446 --> 00:13:27,046
Officer Takagi, Pops asked me to do this.

197
00:13:27,046 --> 00:13:30,146
What? But Mr. Mouri's over there.

198
00:13:30,146 --> 00:13:32,146
It's okay...

199
00:13:33,646 --> 00:13:37,946
Pops! I brought everyone over just like you told me to.

200
00:13:37,946 --> 00:13:41,246
What on earth is this about, Mouri?

201
00:13:41,246 --> 00:13:43,246
I've finally figured it out.

202
00:13:43,246 --> 00:13:47,646
The truth behind this murder disguised as an accident.

203
00:13:48,946 --> 00:13:53,346
But the crime scene has all the signs of an accident!

204
00:13:53,346 --> 00:13:55,746
Why do you think it was murder?

205
00:13:55,746 --> 00:13:56,846
The bruise.

206
00:13:56,846 --> 00:14:00,046
The bruise? Do you mean the bruise on the corpse?

207
00:14:00,046 --> 00:14:03,346
He got it when he fell off the ladder, isn't it?

208
00:14:03,346 --> 00:14:05,646
That's what I thought at first.

209
00:14:05,646 --> 00:14:09,446
But this statue helped me get at the truth.

210
00:14:09,446 --> 00:14:11,346
Please take a good look.

211
00:14:11,346 --> 00:14:13,246
Its nose is chipped, you see that?

212
00:14:13,246 --> 00:14:15,746
It certainly is. But...

213
00:14:15,746 --> 00:14:17,746
The nose is chipped not long ago.

214
00:14:17,746 --> 00:14:22,246
It's as if something hit it with a lot of force recently.

215
00:14:22,246 --> 00:14:23,446
It couldn't be...

216
00:14:23,446 --> 00:14:27,346
Yes. Everything should come to light after re-investigation.

217
00:14:27,346 --> 00:14:29,046
The bruise on the corpse's cheek

218
00:14:29,046 --> 00:14:32,046
was made after it hit the nose of the statue.

219
00:14:32,046 --> 00:14:34,546
But the corpse was found...

220
00:14:34,546 --> 00:14:35,746
Yes.

221
00:14:35,746 --> 00:14:39,346
If Mr. Kataoka really fell off the ladder,

222
00:14:39,346 --> 00:14:43,046
he couldn't have hit this statue that is so far away.

223
00:14:43,046 --> 00:14:47,746
Exactly. Mr. Kataoka didn't fall off the ladder.

224
00:14:47,746 --> 00:14:52,446
First, he was struck and passed out by the killer here.

225
00:14:52,446 --> 00:14:55,046
Then, he was carried over to the place where his body was found.

226
00:14:55,046 --> 00:14:58,346
And the killer murdered him by hitting his head and body

227
00:14:58,346 --> 00:15:00,546
against the stone paving.

228
00:15:00,546 --> 00:15:04,546
After that, the killer put Mr. Kataoka's shoe prints on the ladder

229
00:15:04,546 --> 00:15:06,946
and put the ladder beside the corpse

230
00:15:06,946 --> 00:15:10,746
to make everyone believed that Mr. Kataoka fell off the ladder.

231
00:15:12,246 --> 00:15:14,346
But who would do that?

232
00:15:14,346 --> 00:15:17,046
There's something I'd like to confirm before that.

233
00:15:17,046 --> 00:15:19,346
Officer Takagi!

234
00:15:19,346 --> 00:15:23,246
Was the edge of Mr. Kataoka's cape torn?

235
00:15:23,246 --> 00:15:25,246
No, it wasn't.

236
00:15:25,246 --> 00:15:28,746
Don't you think it's strange, Ran?

237
00:15:28,746 --> 00:15:29,746
I get it!

238
00:15:29,746 --> 00:15:31,646
What do you mean?

239
00:15:31,646 --> 00:15:34,946
Mr. Kataoka's cape was supposed to be ripped!

240
00:15:34,946 --> 00:15:36,046
Watch out!

241
00:15:42,046 --> 00:15:45,446
But, the cape the corpse was wearing wasn't torn.

242
00:15:45,446 --> 00:15:47,446
But why?

243
00:15:47,446 --> 00:15:49,346
The answer is simple.

244
00:15:49,346 --> 00:15:53,346
It's because the person you were going after wasn't Mr. Kataoka!

245
00:15:53,346 --> 00:15:55,246
-What? -What?

246
00:15:55,246 --> 00:15:59,846
Of course, the first Thief K that we were chasing was Mr. Kataoka.

247
00:15:59,846 --> 00:16:03,446
But, someone took over his place part way,

248
00:16:03,446 --> 00:16:05,846
the killer switched with Mr. Kataoka.

249
00:16:05,846 --> 00:16:09,146
Isn't that right? The other Thief K,

250
00:16:09,146 --> 00:16:12,946
as well as the one who killed Mr. Kataoka...

251
00:16:12,946 --> 00:16:15,346
Mr. Makoto Sada!

252
00:16:15,346 --> 00:16:21,646
But Mr. Sada was with us while chasing after Mr. Kataoka.

253
00:16:21,646 --> 00:16:23,646
I don't think he had time to switch with Mr. Kataoka.

254
00:16:23,646 --> 00:16:26,646
No, you weren't always with him.

255
00:16:26,646 --> 00:16:28,946
There was one time you parted ways,

256
00:16:28,946 --> 00:16:31,346
just before you came to this backyard.

257
00:16:32,546 --> 00:16:35,346
You two go around from that side!

258
00:16:35,346 --> 00:16:37,046
We can trap him for sure this time.

259
00:16:37,046 --> 00:16:38,746
Okay.

260
00:16:38,746 --> 00:16:42,046
This was probably Mr. Kataoka's idea to begin with.

261
00:16:42,046 --> 00:16:46,546
He probably had that switching plan for our game.

262
00:16:46,546 --> 00:16:49,346
But, Mr. Sada's purpose

263
00:16:49,346 --> 00:16:54,446
was to take advantage of this trick and kill Mr. Kataoka.

264
00:16:54,446 --> 00:16:55,946
After watching Ran and Conan go off,

265
00:16:55,946 --> 00:16:57,946
he took a short cut into the residence

266
00:16:57,946 --> 00:17:02,446
and wore the outfit of Thief K that he had prepared beforehand,

267
00:17:02,446 --> 00:17:08,046
then attacked Mr. Kataoka who was waiting for him from behind

268
00:17:08,046 --> 00:17:10,246
and hid him in the shade of the statue.

269
00:17:10,246 --> 00:17:13,446
After that, Mr. Sada appears before Ran and Conan as Thief K!

270
00:17:13,446 --> 00:17:16,546
Then, the one we were chasing after...

271
00:17:16,546 --> 00:17:19,746
It wasn't Mr. Kataoka but Mr. Sada.

272
00:17:19,746 --> 00:17:22,046
I confirmed with the kid a while ago.

273
00:17:22,046 --> 00:17:24,346
Thief K's shoes were supposed to be muddy

274
00:17:24,346 --> 00:17:25,746
because he ran through the underground passage,

275
00:17:25,746 --> 00:17:29,846
but the pedal of the bike was clean.

276
00:17:29,846 --> 00:17:32,946
Then, Mr. Sada removed that outfit

277
00:17:32,946 --> 00:17:35,446
and act as if nothing had happened.

278
00:17:35,446 --> 00:17:38,746
Mr. Mouri, you've forgotten something very important!

279
00:17:38,746 --> 00:17:40,946
I heard Mr. Kataoka's scream

280
00:17:40,946 --> 00:17:45,446
and the sound of the ladder falling together with Ran and Conan.

281
00:17:45,446 --> 00:17:48,746
Are you referring to this?

282
00:17:48,746 --> 00:17:49,946
Officer Takagi!

283
00:17:49,946 --> 00:17:51,346
Yes, sir!

284
00:17:57,946 --> 00:18:01,946
No doubt about it. That's the voice and noise we heard!

285
00:18:01,946 --> 00:18:04,746
It was the sound from the stereo.

286
00:18:04,746 --> 00:18:08,146
Mr. Sada recorded Mr. Kataoka's voice

287
00:18:08,146 --> 00:18:11,246
and the sound of the ladder falling into a CD beforehand

288
00:18:11,246 --> 00:18:15,646
and used a timer to set it so that it would play

289
00:18:15,646 --> 00:18:17,646
at that time at top volume.

290
00:18:17,646 --> 00:18:22,946
But, Mr. Kataoka was still alive at the time.

291
00:18:22,946 --> 00:18:25,246
He is hidden in the shade of this statue.

292
00:18:25,246 --> 00:18:27,946
Don't tell me that it was when we went into the residence

293
00:18:27,946 --> 00:18:30,146
to look for Mr. Kataoka...

294
00:18:30,146 --> 00:18:35,146
Yes, Mr. Sada came to the backyard and killed Mr. Kataoka.

295
00:18:35,146 --> 00:18:39,246
Then he schemed a plan to deceive everyone.

296
00:18:39,246 --> 00:18:41,446
He also carried Mr. Kataoka's corpse

297
00:18:41,446 --> 00:18:42,746
because he wanted to deceive everyone

298
00:18:42,746 --> 00:18:44,446
about the blood that had splattered on his clothes.

299
00:18:44,446 --> 00:18:45,946
Isn't that right?

300
00:18:47,146 --> 00:18:52,746
Mr. Sada, your mistake is by setting the stereo volume too high.

301
00:18:52,746 --> 00:18:56,746
The sound was so loud that it reached us, who were at a distance,

302
00:18:56,746 --> 00:18:59,946
as well as Seiya who was listening to music using headphones.

303
00:18:59,946 --> 00:19:03,446
In fact, the voices of people are not audible at such distance.

304
00:19:03,446 --> 00:19:06,346
But what are you trying to imply?

305
00:19:06,346 --> 00:19:08,546
That doesn't serve as proof.

306
00:19:08,546 --> 00:19:11,446
You are right. So, let me show you something now.

307
00:19:11,446 --> 00:19:15,346
A conclusive proof that you are the killer.

308
00:19:17,246 --> 00:19:19,746
After you had finished your act,

309
00:19:19,746 --> 00:19:23,546
I'm sure you had to hide your outfit

310
00:19:23,546 --> 00:19:25,746
somewhere at the crossroad with a bronze statue.

311
00:19:25,746 --> 00:19:29,546
In fact, a hidden hole was found in the pedestal of the statue,

312
00:19:29,546 --> 00:19:31,646
but it was empty.

313
00:19:31,646 --> 00:19:33,046
Of course.

314
00:19:33,046 --> 00:19:35,046
Yes, because that place was used only

315
00:19:35,046 --> 00:19:39,746
to hide something that you needed in order to hide your outfit.

316
00:19:39,746 --> 00:19:46,346
Back then, you hid your outfit in the thing you took out of the hole!

317
00:19:59,946 --> 00:20:02,446
Don't you think this ball is strange?

318
00:20:02,446 --> 00:20:06,746
It seems a bit too large and it's making a strange sound.

319
00:20:11,846 --> 00:20:13,646
This is...

320
00:20:15,946 --> 00:20:18,046
A piece of cracked marble.

321
00:20:18,046 --> 00:20:20,446
Although slight, there's blood on it.

322
00:20:20,446 --> 00:20:22,746
There's gray hair on the wig too.

323
00:20:22,746 --> 00:20:26,446
What is this, Mr. Sada?

324
00:20:28,446 --> 00:20:30,046
Back then,

325
00:20:30,046 --> 00:20:32,046
you took that ball out of the hole of the pedestal,

326
00:20:32,046 --> 00:20:35,046
hid the outfit in it

327
00:20:35,046 --> 00:20:38,346
and threw it in a blind spot from Ran and Conan.

328
00:20:38,346 --> 00:20:42,246
You were probably planning to retrieve it later.

329
00:20:42,246 --> 00:20:44,446
But, you miscalculated two things.

330
00:20:44,446 --> 00:20:50,346
The first was the stray cat rolled the ball somewhere.

331
00:20:50,346 --> 00:20:55,346
And the second was the chipped piece of the marbled nose

332
00:20:55,346 --> 00:21:00,046
that you had to hide was making strange noises from the ball.

333
00:21:00,046 --> 00:21:03,346
No, my biggest miscalculation was

334
00:21:03,346 --> 00:21:06,746
underestimating your deduction skills, Mr. Mouri.

335
00:21:06,746 --> 00:21:07,746
You mean...

336
00:21:07,746 --> 00:21:11,746
Yes, I'm the one who killed Mr. Kataoka.

337
00:21:11,746 --> 00:21:13,646
-But... -Why?

338
00:21:13,646 --> 00:21:16,746
I couldn't forgive him.

339
00:21:16,746 --> 00:21:20,246
He lived a capricious life

340
00:21:20,246 --> 00:21:25,346
as if he had forgotten all about his late wife.

341
00:21:25,346 --> 00:21:27,946
I felt sorry for his late wife.

342
00:21:27,946 --> 00:21:29,246
You're wrong.

343
00:21:29,246 --> 00:21:30,446
What?

344
00:21:30,446 --> 00:21:35,646
The only things he loved were detectives and his late wife.

345
00:21:35,646 --> 00:21:39,446
Although it seemed he married me to get rid of his sadness,

346
00:21:39,446 --> 00:21:43,046
I couldn't fill his empty space no matter how much I tried.

347
00:21:43,046 --> 00:21:46,646
I only just realised the truth recently.

348
00:21:46,646 --> 00:21:50,646
That's why you took off your marriage ring.

349
00:21:50,646 --> 00:21:53,446
It was just an act of slight protest.

350
00:21:53,446 --> 00:21:57,446
But, he didn't even notice it.

351
00:21:58,446 --> 00:22:00,346
I see.

352
00:22:00,346 --> 00:22:03,746
Master did love his wife.

353
00:23:25,846 --> 00:23:27,046
"Mouri Detective Agency"

354
00:23:27,046 --> 00:23:31,646
So, is this the reward that Mr. Kataoka had ready?

355
00:23:32,646 --> 00:23:37,946
I guess he truly was a fool to make something like this!

356
00:23:37,946 --> 00:23:43,046
I just enjoyed taking on his challenges.

357
00:23:43,046 --> 00:23:45,446
Dad.

358
00:23:45,446 --> 00:23:48,446
So...

359
00:23:48,446 --> 00:23:50,746
What're you going to do with this?

360
00:23:51,746 --> 00:23:53,246
"Next Episode"

361
00:23:53,246 --> 00:23:56,046
Hey... Don't tell me...

362
00:23:56,046 --> 00:23:57,146
Conan?

363
00:24:00,546 --> 00:24:03,046
I told you, we came to get Conan's clothes,

364
00:24:03,046 --> 00:24:06,446
and found that Matsunosuke asleep!

365
00:24:06,446 --> 00:24:08,946
Everybody's made a mistake.

366
00:24:08,946 --> 00:24:12,046
Even the witness and the murderer too.

367
00:24:12,046 --> 00:24:13,946
I see!

368
00:24:13,946 --> 00:24:16,446
I get the picture.

369
00:24:16,446 --> 00:24:17,946
Next Conan,

370
00:24:17,946 --> 00:24:19,946
"Promenade"

371
00:24:37,446 --> 00:24:39,746
Next Conan's Hint:

372
00:24:39,746 --> 00:24:42,046
"Walking the dog"

373
00:24:42,046 --> 00:24:44,646
-Hey, let's get a dog. -No, dad is a good enough guard dog already.

374
00:24:44,646 --> 00:24:46,946
-Woof! -Good boy... Get back in your kennel.

